parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body Sensor and Accelerator Pedal Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body sensor and accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or suddenly accelerate without warning, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may go into limp mode
the accelerator pedal may stick to the floor
the vehicle may stall or suddenly accelerate without warning
and the check engine light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the climate control and radio can cause the vehicle's heating and cooling system to malfunction, leading to discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The heating and cooling system may not function properly
the radio may not turn on
and the dashboard lights may flicker or go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience sudden acceleration without warning, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may stall
lose power
or experience sudden acceleration without warning
the dashboard lights may flicker or go out
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
the brake lights may not function properly
and the vehicle may experience sudden acceleration without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system and frame damage can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbags may not deploy properly
the frame may be bent or damaged
and the vehicle may experience electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to catastrophic engine failure, loss of power, and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The temperature gauge rises rapidly
the vehicle overheats
steam comes out of the engine
the engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Water Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to fail, resulting in costly repairs or replacement, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle experiences a loss of power steering and brakes
and the engine may seize or hydro lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause coolant to leak into the engine oil, leading to catastrophic engine failure, loss of power, and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine oil becomes contaminated with coolant
the engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fault warning message appears on the instrument panel
the steering wheel seizes
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
the power steering fluid leaks under the vehicle
and the traction control light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear assembly can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fault warning message appears on the instrument panel
the steering wheel seizes
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
and the traction control light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical power steering motor can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fault warning message appears on the instrument panel
the steering wheel seizes
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
and the traction control light comes on.
